 **Ansible**

Ansible is an open-source configuration management, application deployment and provisioning tool that uses its own declarative language in YAML.
Ansible is agentless, meaning you only need remote connections via SSH or Windows Remote Management via Powershell in order to function

Visit the following resources to learn more:

- [Ansible Website](https://www.ansible.com/)
- [Official Documentation](https://docs.ansible.com/)
- [Ansible Getting Started Guide](https://www.ansible.com/resources/get-started)
- [Ansible Full Course for Beginners](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9Ua2b06oAr4)


- **system Requirements**
    - Control Node:
        - Python2.7 or Python3.5+
        - SSH
    - Managed Nodes:
        - Python 2.6+ or Python3.5+
        - SSH

- **Setup and Configuration**
    - Method1: pip
        
        ```bash
        apt install -y python3-pip  python3-venv
        python -m venv <env-name>
        source <env-name>/bin/activate
        #update pip
        pip install -U pip 
        pip install ansible
        ```
        
    - Method2: apt
        
        ```bash
        apt install -y software-properties-common
        apt-add-repository --yes --update ppa:ansible/ansible
        apt install -y ansible
        ```
        
